com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.venues

Class ShareVenueRequestExecutor

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.RequestExecutor<java.lang.String>
      • com.kontakt.sdk.android.cloud.api.executor.venues.ShareVenueRequestExecutor

  • public class ShareVenueRequestExecutor
extends RequestExecutor<java.lang.String>
    Request executor provided by VenuesApi. Use this class if you want to share venues to managers through fluent API in chained fashion, for example: 
       
   IKontaktCloud kontaktCloud = KontaktCloud.newInstance();
   kontaktCloud.venues().share(IDs)
      .toManagers(managerEmails)
      .withAccess(Access.VIEWER)
      .expirationDate(date)
      .execute();
    Keep in mind that managers and access must be specified so invocations of toManagers and withAccess methods are mandatory. Moreover, the Access.OWNER and Access.SUPERVISOR values are prohibited as an input parameters of withAccess method. All conditions must be fulfilled, otherwise an exception will be thrown at runtime.
